  <h2>Lecturer</h2>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <td><h3>Ede Zimmermann</h3>
            <div class="portrait" style="margin: 0 10px 10px 0"><img src="/images/250/ede-zimmermann.jpg" /></div>
        </td>
        <td>
            <div style="margin: 4px 0"><b>Email:</b> tezimmer (AT) uni-frankfurt (DOT) de</div>
            <div style="margin: 4px 0"><b>Homepage:</b> <a href="http://web.uni-frankfurt.de/fb10/zimmermann/">http://web.uni-frankfurt.de/fb10/zimmermann/</a></div>
            <h4>Bio:</h4>
            <p>Thomas Ede Zimmermann graduated from Konstanz University in 1987 and has since held academic positions at various universities. Since 1999, he is a professor of formal semantics in the linguistics department of Goethe University, Frankfurt. He has made various descriptive and foundational contributions to formal semantics. His main areas of research include intensional constructions, the theory of reference, and the formal aspects of semantic complexity.
<p>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>

